@Node "ARexx" "wookie_arexx.guide/ARexx"
@Toc "Main"

WookieChat's ARexx Port
***********************

Overview
========

WookieChat supports a versatile ARexx Port.

- Command reference -

 @{" RX_SAY " Link "RX_SAY"}               SAY              Send text to a channel or private tab
 @{" RX_SAYALL " Link "RX_SAYALL"}            SAYALL           Send text to all channels on all networks
 @{" RX_COMMAND " Link "RX_COMMAND"}           COMMAND          Execute a command like you have just typed it in WookieChat
 @{" RX_GETMYNICK " Link "RX_GETMYNICK"}         GETMYNICK        Request current nick name.
 @{" RX_ISCONNECTED " Link "RX_ISCONNECTED"}       ISCONNECTED      Check whether connection is established.
 @{" RX_GETSERVERNAME " Link "RX_GETSERVERNAME"}     GETSERVERNAME    Request current server name.
 @{" RX_ECHO " Link "RX_ECHO"}              ECHO             Echos text to the current listview.
 @{" RX_RAW " Link "RX_RAW"}               RAW              Sends raw text to the server.
 @{" RX_CHANNELS " Link "RX_CHANNELS"}          CHANNELS         Returns string showing joined channels.
 @{" RX_GETCHANNEL " Link "RX_GETCHANNEL"}        GETCHANNEL       Returns channel joined in active window.
 @{" RX_GETNETWORK " Link "RX_GETNETWORK"}          GETNETWORK     Returns information for active network
 @{" RX_GETSELECTEDUSER " Link "RX_GETSELECTEDUSER"}   GETSELECTEDUSER  Returns nick of user selected in userlist window.
 @{" RX_GETUSER " Link "RX_GETUSER"}           GETUSER          Returns the nick of user number in userlist window.
 @{" RX_GETUSERS " Link "RX_GETUSERS"}          GETUSERS         Returns a string with all users in the current channel.
 @{" RX_GETUSERSTATE " Link "RX_GETUSERSTATE"}      GETUSERSTATE     Tells whether the user has Op, Voice, or no privledges.
 @{" RX_GETLINE " Link "RX_GETLINE"}           GETLINE          Waits for the next line and parses it into a stem variable.
 @{" RX_GETLINECOUNT " Link "RX_GETLINECOUNT"}      GETLINECOUNT     Tells you how many lines have been entered since you entered the channel.
 @{" RX_GETLASTLINE " Link "RX_GETLASTLINE"}       GETLASTLINE      Returns the last line, unparsed.
 @{" RX_GETAWAYSTATE " Link "RX_GETAWAYSTATE"}      GETAWAYSTATE     Checks if you are marked away.
 @{" RX_GETVERSION " Link "RX_GETVERSION"}        GETVERSION       Tells you what version WookieChat you are using.
 @{" RX_GETCTCPSOUNDDIR " Link "RX_GETCTCPSOUNDDIR"}   GETCTCPSOUNDDIR  Returns CTCP sounds directory.
 @{" RX_GETDCCRECEIVEDIR " Link "RX_GETDCCRECEIVEDIR"}  GETDCCRECEIVEDIR Returns DCC receive directory.
 @{" RX_PLAYSOUND " Link "RX_PLAYSOUND"}         PLAYSOUND        Plays a sound via WookieChat.
 @{" RX_PARSELINE " Link "RX_PARSELINE"}         PARSELINE        Returns the line given in a stem variable.


@EndNode

@Node "RX_SAY" "wookie_arexx.guide/RX_SAY"
@Next "RX_SAYALL"
@Toc "ARexx"

SAY
===

Usage:
     SAY NETWORK/K,CHANNEL/K,TEXT/F

DESCRIPTION:

Sends @{b}TEXT@{ub} to the specified channel and network.

CHANNEL/K is to specify a certain channel to direct your SAY output to.

The network field is for when you are on multiple IRC networks, and you wish
to direct the command to a paricular network. NETWORK=CURRENT will always
specify the network currently being displayed in WookieChat. Otherwise, a
number must be used. NETWORK=0 for the first IRC network you're on, NETWORK=1
for the second, etc. Note: If no NETWORK parameter is specified, then it
will assume you wish to use NETWORK=CURRENT.

EXAMPLES:

     'say NETWORK=CURRENT CHANNEL=#amigaworld I hate Amigas!'

RELATED TOPICS: See @{"RX_ECHO" Link "RX_ECHO"}.


@EndNode

@Node "RX_SAYALL" "wookie_arexx.guide/RX_SAYALL"
@Next "RX_GETMYNICK"
@Toc "ARexx"

SAYALL
======

Usage:
     SAYALL TEXT/F/A

DESCRIPTION:

Sends @{b}TEXT@{ub} to all channels on all IRC networks currently connected to

EXAMPLES:

     'sayall I hate Amigas!'

RELATED TOPICS: See @{"RX_ECHO" Link "RX_ECHO"}.


@EndNode


@Node "RX_COMMAND" "wookie_arexx.guide/RX_COMMAND"
@Next "RX_GETMYNICK"
@Toc "ARexx"

COMMAND
=======

Usage:
     COMMAND NETWORK/K,TEXT/F/A

DESCRIPTION:

Sends @{b}TEXT@{ub} to WookieChat as if you had just typed it manually

The network field is for when you are on multiple IRC networks, and you wish
to direct the command to a paricular network. NETWORK=CURRENT will always
specify the network currently being displayed in WookieChat. Otherwise, a
number must be used. NETWORK=0 for the first IRC network you're on, NETWORK=1
for the second, etc. Note: If no NETWORK parameter is specified, then it
will assume you wish to use NETWORK=CURRENT.

EXAMPLES:

     'command NETWORK=CURRENT /dcc send jahc sys:c/list'

RELATED TOPICS: See @{"RX_ECHO" Link "RX_ECHO"}.


@EndNode


@Node "RX_ISCONNECTED" "wookie_arexx.guide/RX_ISCONNECTED"
@Next "RX_GETSERVERNAME"
@Prev "RX_GETMYNICK"
@Toc "ARexx"

ISCONNECTED
===========

Usage:
     ISCONNECTED NETWORK/K

DESCRIPTION:

Checks whether a connection is currently established. Returns RC 0 if
the link is up, RC 5 otherwise.

The network field is for when you are on multiple IRC networks, and you wish
to direct the command to a paricular network. NETWORK=CURRENT will always
specify the network currently being displayed in WookieChat. Otherwise, a
number must be used. NETWORK=0 for the first IRC network you're on, NETWORK=1
for the second, etc. Note: If no NETWORK parameter is specified, then it
will assume you wish to use NETWORK=CURRENT.

EXAMPLES:

     "ISCONNECTED";"ECHO" rc
     "ISCONNECTED NETWORK=CURRENT";"ECHO" rc

RELATED TOPICS:


@EndNode

