@Node "RX_USERHOST" "wookie_arexx.guide/RX_USERHOST"
@Next "RX_ECHO"
@Prev "RX_GETSERVERNAME"
@Toc "ARexx"

USERHOST
========

Usage:
     USERHOST NICK/A

DESCRIPTION:

Returns the userhost specification belonging to @{b}NICK@{ub}.  Wookie keeps an
internal list of the userhosts of every nick that occurred yet. You can
query this database with this command.  Note however that it is
possible that the userhost isn't in the database yet; this command will
@{i}not@{ui} query the server then, but simply return an error.

EXAMPLES:

     "USERHOST jahc";"ECHO" result

RELATED TOPICS: See @{"RX_GETMYNICK" Link "RX_GETMYNICK"}.


@EndNode

@Node "RX_ECHO" "wookie_arexx.guide/RX_ECHO"
@Next "RX_RAW"
@Prev "RX_USERHOST"
@Toc "ARexx"

ECHO
====

Usage:
     ECHO NETWORK/K,COLOUR/K,TEXT/F/A

DESCRIPTION:

The network field is for when you are on multiple IRC networks, and you wish
to direct the command to a paricular network. NETWORK=CURRENT will always
specify the network currently being displayed in WookieChat. Otherwise, a
number must be used. NETWORK=0 for the first IRC network you're on, NETWORK=1
for the second, etc. Note: If no NETWORK parameter is specified, then it
will assume you wish to use NETWORK=CURRENT.

Sends text to the listview. With COLOUR you can set any of the colours set in
the WookieChat configuration. The colours you can use are :

@{b}COLOUR=0 : background@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=1 : nicklist background@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=2 : join@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=3 : part@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=4 : quit@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=5 : modes@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=6 : CTCP@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=7 : actions@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=8 : normal text@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=9 : info@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=10 : own text@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=11 : highlight@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=12 : notices@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=13 : invite@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=14 : kick@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=15 : nickchange@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=16 : topic@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=17 : wallops@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=18 : activity@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=19 : chat activity@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=20 : highlight activity@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=21 : nicklist text@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=22 : listview tabs background@{ub}
@{b}COLOUR=23 : listview tabs text pen@{ub}

EXAMPLES:

     "ECHO COLOUR=3 This is echo test using the part message pen"


@EndNode

