GETNETWORK
==========

Usage:
     GETNETWORK

DESCRIPTION:

Returns the following stem variables for the active network:
    NETWORK.GROUPNAME  = If you have connected to a server from the Server
                        Selection window, its group name will be specified
                        here

    NETWORK.SERVERNAME = The name of the server you're connected to

    NETWORK.NUMBER     = Each IRC network in WookieChat will have its own number
                        The first network will equal 0, the second will equal 1,
                        etc.

EXAMPLES:

     options results;"getnetwork";"ECHO" network.servername; "ECHO" network.number


RELATED TOPICS: See @{"RX_CHANNELS" Link "RX_CHANNELS"}, @{"RX_NETWORKS" Link "RX_NETWORKS"}.


@EndNode


@Node "RX_GETNETWORK" "wookie_arexx.guide/RX_GETNETWORK"
@Next ""
@Prev ""
@Toc "ARexx"

NETWORKS
========

Usage:
     NETWORKS

DESCRIPTION:
    Returns the amount of IRC networks currently open or connected to.
    If you are only on 1 IRC network, then it will return 0. If you are
    on 3, it will return 2.

USAGE
    options results;"networks";"ECHO Number of networks currently on:" result

@EndNode


