GETSELECTEDUSER
===============

Usage:
     GETSELECTEDUSER NETWORK/K,CHANNEL/K

DESCRIPTION:

Returns the Nick the user highlighted in the userlist window.

The network field is for when you are on multiple IRC networks, and you wish
to direct the command to a paricular network. NETWORK=CURRENT will always
specify the network currently being displayed in WookieChat. Otherwise, a
number must be used. NETWORK=0 for the first IRC network you're on, NETWORK=1
for the second, etc. Note: If no NETWORK parameter is specified, then it
will assume you wish to use NETWORK=CURRENT.

If the CHANNEL argument is specified, the selected user in that channel will
be returned.

EXAMPLES:

     options results;"getselecteduser";"ECHO" result

     options results;"getselecteduser CHANNEL=#amiga";"ECHO" result

     options results;"getselecteduser NETWORK=CURRENT CHANNEL=#amiga";"ECHO" result

RELATED TOPICS: See @{"RX_GETUSER" Link "RX_GETUSER"}, @{"RX_GETUSERS" Link "RX_GETUSERS"}, @{"RX_GETWINNUM" Link "RX_GETWINNUM"}.


@EndNode

@Node "RX_GETUSER" "wookie_arexx.guide/RX_GETUSER"
@Next "RX_GETUSERS"
@Prev "RX_GETSELECTEDUSER"
@Toc "ARexx"

GETUSER
=======

Usage
     GETUSER NETWORK/K,USER/A,CHANNEL/K

DESCRIPTION:

Returns the nick of the user number given on the specified channel
userlist.

The network field is for when you are on multiple IRC networks, and you wish
to direct the command to a paricular network. NETWORK=CURRENT will always
specify the network currently being displayed in WookieChat. Otherwise, a
number must be used. NETWORK=0 for the first IRC network you're on, NETWORK=1
for the second, etc. Note: If no NETWORK parameter is specified, then it
will assume you wish to use NETWORK=CURRENT.

Keep in mind, the userlist starts from 0!

EXAMPLES:

     options results; "getuser NETWORK=0 CHANNEL=#amigaworld"; "ECHO" result


RELATED TOPICS: See @{"RX_GETSELECTEDUSER" Link "RX_GETSELECTEDUSER"}, @{"RX_GETUSERS" Link "RX_GETUSERS"}, @{"RX_GETWINNUM" Link "RX_GETWINNUM"}.


@EndNode

