@Node "RX_MATCHUSERHOST" "wookie_arexx.guide/RX_MATCHUSERHOST"
@Next "RX_PLAYSOUND"
@Prev "RX_GETDCCRECEIVEDIR"
@Toc "ARexx"

MATCHUSERHOST
=============

Usage
     MATCHUSERHOST USERHOST/A,PATTERN/A

DESCRIPTION:

Matches userhost with pattern and sets rc to 0 if there is no match and
rc to 1 if there is a match.  USERHOST @{i}must@{ui} be a real host like
nick!user@hostname and not a pattern.  PATTERN may hold special
characters like "*" and "?" such as ni*!use?@ho?tna*.

EXAMPLES:

     options results
     "MATCHUSERHOST Joe!Joeshmoe@ppp100.net.il *!*@*.net.il"
     "ECHO" rc


@EndNode

@Node "RX_PLAYSOUND" "wookie_arexx.guide/RX_PLAYSOUND"
@Next "RX_PARSELINE"
