@Toc "ARexx"

PLAYSOUND
=========

Usage
     PLAYSOUND NETWORK/K,FILENAME/F/A

DESCRIPTION:

This command will play a sound via WookieChat.  It may play a sound-file if
you give it a filename.  You don't have to give a complete file name,
you can give one that is in the sounds directory.

The network field is for when you are on multiple IRC networks, and you wish
to direct the command to a paricular network. NETWORK=CURRENT will always
specify the network currently being displayed in WookieChat. Otherwise, a
number must be used. NETWORK=0 for the first IRC network you're on, NETWORK=1
for the second, etc. Note: If no NETWORK parameter is specified, then it
will assume you wish to use NETWORK=CURRENT.

EXAMPLES:

     "PLAYSOUND Hello.WAV"

     "PLAYSOUND NETWORK=CURRENT Hello.WAV"


@EndNode

@Node "RX_PARSELINE" "wookie_arexx.guide/RX_PARSELINE"
@Prev "RX_PLAYSOUND"
@Toc "ARexx"

PARSELINE
=========

Usage
     PARSELINE LINE/F/A

DESCRIPTION:

Parses the line specified and returns the following stem variables;
     LINE         = The entire, unparsed, line received.

     LINE.PREFIX  = The Nick and user@host

     LINE.COMMAND = The MSG Type

     LINE.DEST    = The channel the message was written to.

     LINE.REST    = The message text.

In certain circumstances, e.g. if you have just recieved a PRIVMSG or
a NOTICE, you will also have valid data in these two stem variables:
     LINE.NICK    = The nick by itself

     LINE.HOSTNAME= The user@host information by itself


EXAMPLES:

     options results

     "getlastline"
     last=result
     "parseline" last

     text=line
     prefix=line.prefix
     comm=line.command
     dest=line.dest
     rest=line.rest

     "ECHO" text prefix comm dest rest

RELATED TOPICS: See @{"RX_GETLINE" Link "RX_GETLINE"}, @{"RX_GETLASTLINE" Link "RX_GETLASTLINE"}.


@EndNode

